{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ὑβρ-ιστής</b>, οῦ, ὁ, <br /> <b>violent, wanton, licentious, insolent man,</b> ὑβριστῇσι.. τῶν μένος αἰὲν ἀτάσθαλον, οὐδὲ δύνανται φυλόπιδος κορέσασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.633; ὑβρισταί τε καὶ ἄγριοι οὐδὲ δίκαιοι ἠὲ φιλόξεινοι 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.120, 9.175, 13.201 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the suitors [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare (ὕβρις 1.1), ὑ. καὶ ἀτάσθαλοι 24.282; στρατὸν ὑβριστὴν Μήδων 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 775; Πέρσαι φύσιν ἐόντες ὑ. 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.89; ἀνδρῶν δυναστέων παῖδες ὑβρισταί [prev. author] 2.32 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; στρατὸν θηρῶν ὑ., of the Centaurs, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 1096 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also in Prose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.14, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 24.15, NT.Rom.1.30, etc.\">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]; in a milder sense, <b>sarcastic,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 355c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> especially, opposed to σώφρων, <b>lustful, lewd,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1068 (_anapaest meter_), 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 3.1.21, etc.; ὁ εἰς ὁτιοῦν ὑ. 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.17 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὑ. πενίης <b>insolent</b> towards.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 9.172b (6th c.AD: Palladas Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 6th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of animals, <b>wanton, restive, unruly,</b> ταῦροι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 743; ἵπποι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.5.62, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 254c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> of natural forces, ὑβριστὴς Τυφάων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 307; Ὑβριστὴν ποταμὸν οὐ ψευδώνυμον 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 717. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> of things, ὑ. οἶνος διὰ νεότητα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Epistulae - Epistolographi” 8 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; μέλι Ἀττικὸν ποιεῖ ὑ. [τὸν πλακοῦντα] makes it <b>proud,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Archestratus Epicus “fragment” 62.18 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; νάρθηκας ὑ., of the Bacchae, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 113 (Lyric poetry).\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —Cf. ὕβριστος near the end","strongNumber":"G5197","accentedUnicode":"ὑβριστής","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5195","matchingForm":"ὑβρίζω","stepTransliteration":"hubrizō","gloss":"to mistreat","_zh_tw_Gloss":"凌辱","_es_Gloss":"maltratar","_zh_Gloss":"凌辱"}],"shortDef":"insolent man, violent man","mediumDef":"insolent man, violent man <br /><b>an overbearing, violent person,</b> <ref='Rom.1.30'>Rom. 1:30;</ref> <ref='1Ti.1.13'>1Tim. 1:13</ref>*","stepGloss":"insolent man","stepTransliteration":"hubristēs","count":2,"_es_Definition":"persona insolente, persona de conducta insultante","_zh_tw_Definition":"傲慢, 暴烈的人","_zh_Definition":"傲慢, 暴烈的人","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"kẻ xúc phạm; một người đàn ông xấc xược; một người nói rất nhiều lời lẽ xúc phạm về người khác. Xem G5195","_zh_tw_Gloss":"侮慢者, 侮慢人","_es_Gloss":"hombre insolente","_zh_Gloss":"侮慢者, 侮慢人"}]}